{"article_id":"LENHrClx3QLLINhm","edus":[{"id":0,"text":"Story highlights","depth":1},{"id":1,"text":"The House approves a compromise budget plan on a 332-94 vote","depth":5},{"id":2,"text":"House Speaker Boehner criticizes conservative groups","depth":6},{"id":3,"text":"that oppose the deal","depth":6},{"id":4,"text":"Bill expected to pass the Senate ,","depth":5},{"id":5,"text":"but margin could be razor thin","depth":5},{"id":6,"text":"The proposal would cut the deficit","depth":4},{"id":7,"text":"and ease some sequester cuts","depth":4},{"id":8,"text":"A compromise federal budget plan","depth":8},{"id":9,"text":"that would remove the threat of a government shutdown for two years","depth":8},{"id":10,"text":"won easy approval Thursday from the Republican-controlled U.S. House .","depth":7},{"id":11,"text":"The deal","depth":9},{"id":12,"text":"worked out by House Budget Chairman Rep. Paul Ryan and Senate Budget Committee Chairwoman Patty Murray","depth":9},{"id":13,"text":"passed on a 332-94 vote","depth":8},{"id":14,"text":"and now goes to the Democratic-led Senate ,","depth":8},{"id":15,"text":"which is expected to approve it next week in a very close vote .","depth":8},{"id":16,"text":"It represented rare convergence between the two parties on government spending after two years of bitter debate and political brinksmanship","depth":6},{"id":17,"text":"that included the 16-day shutdown in October .","depth":6},{"id":18,"text":"A White House statement said","depth":7},{"id":19,"text":"the measure does not include everything","depth":9},{"id":20,"text":"President Barack Obama called for ,","depth":9},{"id":21,"text":"but `` it marks an important moment of bipartisan cooperation","depth":9},{"id":22,"text":"and shows","depth":10},{"id":23,"text":"Washington can and should stop governing by crisis","depth":11},{"id":24,"text":"and both sides can work together","depth":12},{"id":25,"text":"to get things done . ''","depth":12},{"id":26,"text":"Public anger over the Washington dysfunction , especially with conservative Republicans","depth":10},{"id":27,"text":"who triggered the shutdown","depth":11},{"id":28,"text":"by trying to link federal spending to their efforts","depth":12},{"id":29,"text":"to dismantle Obamacare ,","depth":12},{"id":30,"text":"motivated GOP leaders to shrug off far right opposition to the budget compromise .","depth":9},{"id":31,"text":"House Speaker John Boehner acknowledged","depth":11},{"id":32,"text":"the measure amounted to only a small step toward the GOP goal","depth":12},{"id":33,"text":"of deficit reduction and balancing the budget ,","depth":12},{"id":34,"text":"but he rejected opposition by some conservatives in his caucus as well as outside groups on the political right .","depth":10},{"id":35,"text":"`` Is it perfect ?","depth":13},{"id":36,"text":"Does it go far enough ?","depth":13},{"id":37,"text":"No , not at all , ''","depth":12},{"id":38,"text":"Boehner said","depth":12},{"id":39,"text":"in urging his colleagues to back the plan ,","depth":12},{"id":40,"text":"noting","depth":11},{"id":41,"text":"it resulted from `` doing what the American people expect us to do","depth":12},{"id":42,"text":"-- coming together","depth":13},{"id":43,"text":"and finding common ground . ''","depth":13},{"id":44,"text":"Ryan noted","depth":8},{"id":45,"text":"that Washington politicians have `` been at each other 's throats for a long time '' over budget issues ,","depth":9},{"id":46,"text":"and Republicans must first win some elections","depth":10},{"id":47,"text":"in order to get all the deficit reduction and spending cuts","depth":11},{"id":48,"text":"they want .","depth":11},{"id":49,"text":"Democrats also hailed the budget proposal as a `` small positive step forward , '' in the words of Rep. Chris Van Hollen of Maryland .","depth":7},{"id":50,"text":"He and other Democrats called for Congress to also extend long-term unemployment benefits for more than 1 million Americans","depth":9},{"id":51,"text":"set to expire after Christmas ,","depth":9},{"id":52,"text":"but their support for the budget plan showed","depth":9},{"id":53,"text":"they dropped any demand","depth":10},{"id":54,"text":"to link the issues in Thursday 's vote .","depth":10},{"id":55,"text":"In the House vote , 169 Republicans voted for the spending plan","depth":10},{"id":56,"text":"while 62 opposed it ,","depth":10},{"id":57,"text":"with 163 Democrats in favor and 32 against .","depth":9},{"id":58,"text":"While most Republicans supported the plan ,","depth":10},{"id":59,"text":"Boehner needed help from Democrats","depth":11},{"id":60,"text":"to get the 217-vote threshold","depth":12},{"id":61,"text":"needed for passage .","depth":12},{"id":62,"text":"Top GOP Senate aides said","depth":15},{"id":63,"text":"they expect the budget to pass the Senate","depth":15},{"id":64,"text":"but it could be by a razor thin margin .","depth":14},{"id":65,"text":"This could also change","depth":14},{"id":66,"text":"if momentum against the bill grows .","depth":14},{"id":67,"text":"GOP conservatives","depth":16},{"id":68,"text":"including Ted Cruz of Texas , Kelly Ayotte of New Hampshire and Lindsey Graham of South Carolina ,","depth":16},{"id":69,"text":"said","depth":15},{"id":70,"text":"they will oppose the measure ,","depth":15},{"id":71,"text":"which would need some Republican support","depth":17},{"id":72,"text":"for Democrats","depth":17},{"id":73,"text":"to overcome an expected filibuster .","depth":16},{"id":74,"text":"`` The new budget deal moves in the wrong direction :","depth":15},{"id":75,"text":"it spends more ,","depth":17},{"id":76,"text":"taxes more ,","depth":18},{"id":77,"text":"and allows continued funding for Obamacare , ''","depth":18},{"id":78,"text":"Cruz said .","depth":16},{"id":79,"text":"`` I can not support it . ''","depth":14},{"id":80,"text":"Graham and Ayotte said","depth":12},{"id":81,"text":"they opposed cuts to pension benefits for some military veterans under the spending plan .","depth":12},{"id":82,"text":"Boehner earlier escalated his criticism of such opposition from conservative colleagues and outside groups in a rare public display of a longstanding rift between the GOP tea party wing and less extreme establishment Republicans .","depth":12},{"id":83,"text":"To Boehner , groups such as Americans for Prosperity lost credibility","depth":14},{"id":84,"text":"by rejecting the plan","depth":15},{"id":85,"text":"before it was announced ,","depth":15},{"id":86,"text":"he told reporters .","depth":13},{"id":87,"text":"He also blamed the influential outside groups for pushing GOP legislators into the politically disastrous government shutdown in October .","depth":12},{"id":88,"text":"`` The day","depth":17},{"id":89,"text":"before the government re-opened ,","depth":17},{"id":90,"text":"one of these groups stood up","depth":16},{"id":91,"text":"and said","depth":16},{"id":92,"text":"'well , we never really thought","depth":17},{"id":93,"text":"it would work , ' ''","depth":17},{"id":94,"text":"he told reporters","depth":14},{"id":95,"text":"before animatedly asking :","depth":14},{"id":96,"text":"`` Are you kidding me ? ''","depth":14},{"id":97,"text":"The agreement","depth":15},{"id":98,"text":"reached by Ryan of Wisconsin and Murray of Washington","depth":15},{"id":99,"text":"would extend government spending into 2015","depth":14},{"id":100,"text":"to remove the threat of another shutdown before next year 's congressional elections .","depth":13},{"id":101,"text":"It sets government spending at $ 1.012 trillion for the current fiscal year","depth":14},{"id":102,"text":"that runs through September ,","depth":14},{"id":103,"text":"and $ 1.014 trillion .","depth":13},{"id":104,"text":"Overall , it proposes to save $ 85 billion","depth":12},{"id":105,"text":"and would reduce the deficit by more than $ 20 billion .","depth":12},{"id":106,"text":"Some conservatives complain","depth":14},{"id":107,"text":"the total is more than the level","depth":15},{"id":108,"text":"called for in the Budget Control Act","depth":16},{"id":109,"text":"that followed brinksmanship negotiations two years ago","depth":17},{"id":110,"text":"over raising the federal borrowing limit .","depth":17},{"id":111,"text":"That 2011 deal imposed unpopular forced spending cuts","depth":14},{"id":112,"text":"known as sequestration on the military and other government programs .","depth":14},{"id":113,"text":"The new compromise would eliminate $ 45 billion from the next round of the sequester cuts","depth":14},{"id":114,"text":"that are set to hit in January ,","depth":14},{"id":115,"text":"as well as another $ 18 billion","depth":14},{"id":116,"text":"scheduled for 2015 .","depth":14},{"id":117,"text":"Boehner noted","depth":13},{"id":118,"text":"it achieves more deficit reduction than the Budget Control Act ,","depth":13},{"id":119,"text":"asserting","depth":13},{"id":120,"text":"it adhered to conservative principles","depth":14},{"id":121,"text":"of shrinking government and federal debt .","depth":14},{"id":122,"text":"`` I 'm as conservative as anybody around this place , ''","depth":11},{"id":123,"text":"he said","depth":12},{"id":124,"text":"in defending his attacks on the outside groups ,","depth":12},{"id":125,"text":"adding","depth":11},{"id":126,"text":"that `` all the things","depth":13},{"id":127,"text":"we 've done in the three years","depth":14},{"id":128,"text":"I 've been Speaker","depth":14},{"id":129,"text":"have not violated any conservative principles , not once . ''","depth":12},{"id":130,"text":"Asked why he spoke out now against the outside groups ,","depth":10},{"id":131,"text":"Boehner said","depth":11},{"id":132,"text":"they crossed a line ,","depth":11},{"id":133,"text":"adding","depth":10},{"id":134,"text":"that `` when you criticize something","depth":12},{"id":135,"text":"and you have no idea what you 're criticizing ,","depth":12},{"id":136,"text":"it undermines your credibility . ''","depth":11},{"id":137,"text":"The White House supports the compromise ,","depth":6},{"id":138,"text":"but factions on both sides still pushed for change","depth":7},{"id":139,"text":"as the issue moved closer to decisive votes .","depth":7},{"id":140,"text":"Liberal Democrats insist","depth":8},{"id":141,"text":"the budget plan should extend long-term unemployment benefits","depth":9},{"id":142,"text":"set to expire at the end of the year .","depth":9},{"id":143,"text":"However , Senate Majority Leader Harry Reid has said","depth":8},{"id":144,"text":"the issue would be considered separately in 2014 .","depth":8},{"id":145,"text":"White House spokesman Jay Carney said","depth":9},{"id":146,"text":"Congress should take up the unemployment insurance extension","depth":9},{"id":147,"text":"but did not insist","depth":9},{"id":148,"text":"that it be part of the budget package .","depth":9},{"id":149,"text":"`` We want them both","depth":9},{"id":150,"text":"and we think","depth":10},{"id":151,"text":"Congress ought to pass them both , ''","depth":10},{"id":152,"text":"Carney said .","depth":8},{"id":153,"text":"Defense Secretary Chuck Hagel praised the agreement Thursday ,","depth":9},{"id":154,"text":"saying","depth":11},{"id":155,"text":"provided certainty for military planning after the harmful sequester cuts and constant showdowns over spending .","depth":11},{"id":156,"text":"`` This agreement does not solve all","depth":14},{"id":157,"text":"( Department of Defense )","depth":14},{"id":158,"text":"budget problems","depth":13},{"id":159,"text":"but it helps address readiness especially in 2014","depth":13},{"id":160,"text":"with putting more money back in training , in particular , and procurement , ''","depth":13},{"id":161,"text":"Hagel said .","depth":11},{"id":162,"text":"`` Time and again , Congress has claimed","depth":11},{"id":163,"text":"that cost-saving measures were permanent ,","depth":11},{"id":164,"text":"only to later renege on these promises , ''","depth":10},{"id":165,"text":"said Jenny Beth Martin , national coordinator of Tea Party Patriots .","depth":9},{"id":166,"text":"She took particular aim at Republican leaders such as Boehner ,","depth":8},{"id":167,"text":"saying","depth":9},{"id":168,"text":"the deal `` also exposes the true colors of several in the GOP establishment","depth":10},{"id":169,"text":"when it comes to protecting conservative principles . ''","depth":10},{"id":170,"text":"Boehner 's comments to reporters were aimed at some of the same organizations","depth":8},{"id":171,"text":"that have effectively pressured House Republicans to resist compromising on budget issues in the past two years .","depth":8},{"id":172,"text":"They include Americans for Prosperity , Club for Growth , Freedom Works , Heritage Action and the Koch brothers , GOP campaign financiers .","depth":7},{"id":173,"text":"He made similar comments","depth":8},{"id":174,"text":"questioning the motives of some of the groups at a closed-door meeting this week with House Republicans .","depth":8},{"id":175,"text":"The Speaker told members","depth":9},{"id":176,"text":"that `` no one controls your voting card but you , ''","depth":9},{"id":177,"text":"according to a GOP source in the meeting .","depth":8},{"id":178,"text":"Strong GOP backing for the budget compromise showed","depth":9},{"id":179,"text":"that conservatives and the outside groups","depth":11},{"id":180,"text":"that back them","depth":11},{"id":181,"text":"have diminished influence .","depth":10},{"id":182,"text":"Rep. John Fleming , a conservative from Louisiana , said","depth":12},{"id":183,"text":"outside groups wo n't be able to sway as many conservatives","depth":12},{"id":184,"text":"because legislators like the idea","depth":12},{"id":185,"text":"of returning Congress to what 's known as regular order","depth":14},{"id":186,"text":"-- deliberating and passing bills the way","depth":15},{"id":187,"text":"they 're supposed to be done ,","depth":15},{"id":188,"text":"instead of backroom deals","depth":14},{"id":189,"text":"reached amid crises .","depth":14},{"id":190,"text":"However , GOP Rep Raul Labrador of Idaho , a critic of the budget plan , wondered","depth":11},{"id":191,"text":"what had changed among fellow Republicans","depth":12},{"id":192,"text":"who now rejected the thinking of the outside conservative groups .","depth":12},{"id":193,"text":"The conservative groups keep scorecards on the voting records of legislators","depth":11},{"id":194,"text":"and back candidates","depth":13},{"id":195,"text":"who follow their policy stances","depth":13},{"id":196,"text":"with key campaign contributions .","depth":12},{"id":197,"text":"Such support can carry enhanced influence with congressional elections","depth":11},{"id":198,"text":"coming up next year .","depth":11},{"id":199,"text":"Dan Holler , a spokesman for Heritage Action , did n't back down from his criticism of the budget deal .","depth":8},{"id":200,"text":"`` Over the next few days , lawmakers will have to explain to their constituents ,","depth":12},{"id":201,"text":"many of whom are our members ,","depth":12},{"id":202,"text":"what they 've achieved","depth":11},{"id":203,"text":"by increasing spending ,","depth":12},{"id":204,"text":"increasing taxes","depth":13},{"id":205,"text":"and offering up another round of promises","depth":14},{"id":206,"text":"waiting to be broken .","depth":14},{"id":207,"text":"That will be a really tough sell back home , ''","depth":11},{"id":208,"text":"Holler said in a statement to CNN .","depth":9}],"relations":[{"parent":417,"left":0,"right":416,"relation":"organization","nuclearity":"SN"},{"parent":416,"left":215,"right":415,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":215,"left":213,"right":214,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":213,"left":211,"right":212,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":211,"left":1,"right":210,"relation":"elaboration","nuclearity":"NS"},{"parent":210,"left":2,"right":3,"relation"